history.content:
Hi Ron-

The faculty are working hard to get this class ready, but as such, I haven't been able to get a syllabus yet. You may need to wait until the class begins.

FYI: This semester (Fall 2014), we never got an official syllabus throughout the ENTIRE semester for EE20! We had no idea what the schedule would be, what materials would be covered, nor do the lectures match the flow of the textbook(difficult to preview/study ahead). All we knew was the date of 2 out of 3 exams (the other exam and the exact times were announced close to the exam date). In the middle of the semester, TA posted a tentative grading plan on piazza and never made it final, which includes the percentage of each item (10% hw, 10% lab, 10% quiz, 20% mt1, 25% each mt2 & mt3, no final). Since we were done after taking midterm3 during the last lecture and no final, they planned to release letter grades during RRR week, but due to 'technical issues', up to this point grades haven't been released yet and nobody knows how they'll curve it, what the cutoffs are, etc.

Thanks,
